VTB Group to Name VTB Capital’s Soloviev First Deputy CEO

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-05-03T14:50:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/vtb-group-to-name-vtb-capital-s-soloviev-first-deputy-ceo-1-.html
Yuri Soloviev, the president of VTB
Capital, will be named first deputy chief executive officer of
the investment company’s parent, VTB Group.  The appointment is subject to the approval of state-
controlled VTB Group’s supervisory council and  Russia ’s central
bank, VTB Capital’s press service said today by e-mail.  Soloviev said in a separate e-mail that part of his
responsibilities in his new role at VTB Group will be overseeing
the investment business. He will also serve as VTB Capital’s
board chairman.  “The investment business is one of VTB Group’s key
strategic lines,” Soloviev said. His continued involvement with
VTB Capital will help “maximize synergies” between VTB Group’s
business lines, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
